SUMMARY:(Maine) Acadia Nat’l Park/Partial Solar Eclipse/Perseids Meteor 
 Shower
DESCRIPTION:Triangle Hiking and Outdoors Group\n**Updated informaion below
  as of 3/12/26**\n\nCome and be a part of one of THOG’s most ambitious t
 rips. This summer adventure in Maine includes Acadia National Park and Bar
  Harbor\, as well as two amazing celestial events- A partial Solar Eclipse
  and the Perseids Meteor Shower.\nThis exciting road trip event will be sl
 ightly different from other THOG events. We will be partnering with Wander
 ful Journeys\, a local travel club that hosts trips to various destination
 s. I decided to team up with them so it would provide us with another laye
 r of resources for planning\, as well as to enhance the trip experience.\n
 **See RSVP requirements below before you register**.\n\n**Highlights of ou
 r weeklong trip will include:**\n-Hikes in Acadia National Park such as Pr
 ecipice Trail and Beehive Trail\n-Thunder Hole\n-Jordan Pond\n-Maine Lobst
 er :)\n-Lighthouses in Maine\n-Viewing the partial Solar Eclipse\n-Watchin
 g the Perseids Meteor Shower (up to 100 per hour this year)\n-Exploring Ba
 r Harbor\n-Bar Island Trail hike- a trail that appears only during low tid
 e\n-Exclusive Swag options for trip participants\n\n**Here is a brief over
 view of our itinerary on this trip** which is subject to change depending 
 on weather and/or other factors:\n8/9- Carpools will meet in a central loc
 ation in the triangle and begin Day 1 of our trip with an overnight stop a
 t a hotel in NJ\n8/10- Continue our trip with a featured stop along the wa
 y at Portland Head Light then arrive at Acadia Nat'l Park/Bar Harbor for e
 ither camping or hotel stay\n8/11- Sunrise at Cadillac Mountain\, hiking c
 hoices in Acadia and other activities then dinner at camp or in Bar Harbor
 \n8/12- **Solar Eclipse/Perseids Meteor Shower Day Activities:** *Watch pa
 rtial Solar Eclipse* near Otter Point\, Explore Bar Harbor\, *Late-night* 
 *watch of Perseids Meteor Shower* near campground at the coast\n8/13- Acti
 vities**:** Sunrise and hike at Otter Point\, Bar Island Trail hike\, Thun
 der Hole\, Jordan Pond\, Sunset at Bass Harbor Head Light Station\n8/14- H
 ead back to NJ to our hotel with a featured stop along the way.\n8/15- Con
 tinue our trip back home with a featured stop along the way.\nAll particip
 ants will be required to pay a $100 deposit to secure their spot on this t
 rip.\n**Accommodations overview:** Everyone will be staying at a designate
 d hotel in NJ going to Maine and returning from Maine.\nIn Maine\, you wil
 l have two stay options:\n-designated Group Campsites (4 nights) that has 
 modern bathrooms\; paid showers are located nearby\n-designated hotel in B
 ar Harbor (4 nights) two beds per room\nIf you choose the hotel stay in Ma
 ine\, it is crucial that you submit your deposit as soon as you RSVP (see 
 rsvp requirements below) to secure your hotel spot due to limited room ava
 ilability. Roommate info/rules will also be in a link that will be sent to
  all who RSVP.\n**Estimated Costs:**\nThe costs below include transportati
 on (gas\, tolls\, parking)\, National Park passes\, Hotel stays during tra
 vel\nCamping- $600-$650 per person\nHotel- $1\,100-$1\,150 per person\nThe
 se best estimates may change depending on the number of attendees and coul
 d decrease or increase. We will notify you of any changes.\n\n**important 
 RSVP requirements:**\n\n1. You will be asked a three-part question as you 
 are RSVPing for this event. Please answer completely!\n2. After you RSVP t
 o this trip\, you will be sent a **link to your email** **address** that w
 ill have questions you need to answer as well as a link to pay your **$100
  deposit (required for every trip participant)**. Links will have all the 
 information about the trip\, total costs per person\, rules on how the dep
 osit works\, itinerary\, trip expectations\, and swag information.\nYour s
 pot on this trip will not be guaranteed until the deposit is paid.\n\nTRIP
  PARTICIPANT WAIVER OF LIABILITY I fully realize that this activity involv
 es a risk of personal injury\, property damage\, or loss of my person or p
 roperty. I hereby for myself\, my heirs\, executors and administrators\, a
 nd same for persons with whom are in my party\, waive and release any clai
 ms or rights against Triangle Hiking & Outdoors Group (THOG)\, all of its 
 owners and coordinators for any and all injury\, damages or loss to my per
 son or property incurred during this activity. I also understand that THOG
  organizers are not required\, nor should it be assumed that they are CPR/
 First Aid/Wilderness Survival Certified and I am responsible for my own pe
 rsonal safety.\n\nWe look forward to having you be a part of this adventur
 e!\nIf you have any questions\, please send me (Larredo) a meetup message 
 or comment below if it is something that could benefit the group. Thanks!\
 nSee you all soon!\nLarredo and Geniece
